As the years went by, Li Wei continued to balance his school life with his duties as a wood elf. He excelled in his studies, earning top grades and becoming a respected student. He also became a skilled protector of the magical forest, using his elven abilities to keep it safe from harm.

One day, a group of loggers threatened to cut down the ancient tree that had transported Li Wei to the magical forest. Li Wei knew that he had to act quickly to save the tree and the forest. He gathered his friends and classmates, explaining the importance of the tree and the magical forest. Together, they organized a protest, raising awareness about the importance of preserving nature.

The protest was a success, and the loggers were forced to abandon their plans. Li Wei's bravery and determination inspired others to take action, and the magical forest was saved. From that day on, Li Wei became a symbol of hope and environmental activism, using his unique abilities to protect the natural world.

In the end, Li Wei found a balance between his school life and his duties as a wood elf. He continued to excel in his studies, while also dedicating his time to protecting the magical forest. And as he looked back on his journey, he knew that he had found his true purpose - to be a guardian of nature and a bridge between the human and elven worlds. [end of text]


